# Refactor: Hexagonal Architecture + DDD + SOLID + Multi-LLM

## Background & Problem Statement

The current codebase uses a 4-layer Clean Architecture (entities вҶ’ use_cases вҶ’ adapters вҶ’ drivers) which is a good start but has several gaps:

1. **No proper DDD constructs** вҖ” missing Aggregates, Value Objects per feature, Domain Events, Domain Services, Factories
2. **Single LLM provider** вҖ” only OpenAI/Anthropic via a global singleton; no per-feature or per-request LLM selection
3. **Hexagonal ports/adapters not explicit** вҖ” input ports (driving) and output ports (driven) are mixed
4. **Coupling in routes** вҖ” routes directly instantiate gateways and AI services instead of using a DI container
5. **Shared concerns in `main.py`** вҖ” exception handlers, middleware, router registration all inline
6. **Some features incomplete** вҖ” `project_manager`, `template_engine`, `usage_tracker` are skeleton-only
7. **No domain events** вҖ” no event-driven communication between features

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Breaking Change**: This refactor changes every feature's directory structure. All imports will change. Existing tests will need updating.

> [!WARNING]
> **Multi-LLM**: Adding HuggingFace/Ollama requires new pip dependencies (`langchain-huggingface`, `langchain-ollama`). Confirm you want all providers installed.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Skeleton features**: `project_manager`, `template_engine`, `usage_tracker` currently have no implementation. Should I implement them fully, or keep them as structured skeletons in the new architecture?

---

